rg/wagn/formatting|Learn more about formatting.]]</em></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{card\'s type+*tform|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>((SHOWS UP if simple or if hard formatted by name))</p>\n<p><strong>By Name<br></strong></p>\n<p><em>Formats any [[tag+plusses|plus card whose name ends in \"+((tagname))\"]]. [[http://wagn.org/wagn/formatting|Learn more about formatting.]]</em></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{+*rform|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>((SHOWS UP if _self+*rform exists and is a Pointer - proposed; see http://wagn.org/wagn/add_plus_star_options_in_config_where_appropriate))</p>\n<p><strong>Auto-complete and default type in Pointers</strong></p>\n<p>Limits the set of cards that Pointer items will auto-complete to. If type is specified, that will be the default for cards created through the Pointer. [[http://wagn.org/wagn/Pointer|Learn more about Pointer auto-complete and default types]]</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{+*options|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>((SHOWS UP on type or simple cards))</p>\n<h1>Help Text</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Editing Cards<br></strong></p>\n<p><em>Help text appears when </em><em>any ((if type -&gt;&nbsp; [type] cards, or ))</em><em> [[_left+plusses|plus card whose name ends in \"+((tag))\"]] is created or edited. [[http://wagn.org/wagn/help_text|Learn more about help text]].<br></em></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{+*edit|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><strong>Creating Cards<br></strong></p>\n<p><em>Help text appears only when any ((if type -&gt;&nbsp; [type] cards, or )) </em><em>[[_left+plusses|</em><em>plus card whose name ends in </em><em> \"+((tag))\"]]</em><em> is created. (This overrides the editing help text above.)<br></em></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{+*new|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>((SHOWS UP on cards inheriting from Basic))</p>\n<h1>Table of Contents<br></h1>\n<p><em><br></em></p>\n<p><em>Manually turn off the table of contents for ((self)). (By default all cards with at least 4 headers have tables of contents.)</em></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{+*table of contents|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>((SHOWS UP on X+*rform of type Pointer))</p>\n<h1>Options</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>This Search defines the pool of cards from which any [[Pointer]] whose name ends in ((left)) auto-completes. If it specifies a type, then any cards created through the Pointer will default to that type. [[http://wagn.org/wagn/Pointer|Learn more about Pointers]].</em></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>{{+*options|closed}}</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(2857,'2012-01-26 12:37:04',206,1,'[[Basic]]\n[[Cardtype]]\n[[Date]]\n[[File]]\n[[HTML]]\n[[Image]]\n[[Number]]\n[[Phrase]]\n[[PlainText]]\n[[Pointer]]\n[[Role]]\n[[Ruby]]\n[[Script]]\n[[Search]]\n[[Toggle]]'),(2862,'2012-01-26 12:37:04',240,1,'{\"type\": \"Cardtype\",\n \"not\": {\"referred_to_by\": \"default cardtype\"},\n \"append\": \"*tform\",\n \"sort\": \"name\"\n}'),(2878,'2012-01-26 12:37:04',241,1,''),(2879,'2012-01-26 12:37:04',242,1,''),(2880,'2012-01-26 12:37:04',243,1,''),(2881,'2012-01-26 12:37:04',244,1,''),(2886,'2012-01-26 12:37:04',245,1,'<p>The maximum number of items allowed in a Pointer. Only works with +*input set to list, checkbox or multiselect.</p>'),(2889,'2012-01-26 12:37:04',247,1,''),(2890,'2012-01-26 12:37:04',248,1,''),(2898,'2012-01-26 12:37:04',246,1,'<p>[[http://wagn.org/wagn/Pointer|Learn more about Pointers\' input interfaces.]]</p>'),(2901,'2012-01-26 12:37:04',253,1,''),(2930,'2012-01-26 12:37:04',257,1,'1'),(2936,'2012-01-26 12:37:04',258,1,'1'),(3001,'2012-01-26 12:37:04',260,1,''),(3002,'2012-01-26 12:37:04',261,1,'{\"right\":\"_self\"}'),(3003,'2012-01-26 12:37:04',262,1,''),(3004,'2012-01-26 12:37:04',263,1,'{\"left\":{\"type\":\"_left\"}, \"right\":\"_right\"}'),(3005,'2012-01-26 12:37:04',264,1,''),(3006,'2012-01-26 12:37:04',265,1,'{\"name\":\"_self\"}'),(3007,'2012-01-26 12:37:04',266,1,''),(3008,'2012-01-26 12:37:04',267,1,'{\"type\":\"_self\"}'),(3009,'2012-01-26 12:37:04',